OL,3,CShortage of BSL interpreters 'putting
OL,4,Cnew law's success in doubt'
OL,6,FA shortage of British Sign Language
OL,7,Finterpreters and translators is a
OL,8,Fsignificant barrier to the success of
OL,9,Fa proposed law to improve access to
OL,10,Fpublic services for Deaf people,
OL,11,Faccording to a Senedd committee.
OL,13,FThe British Sign Language Bill was
OL,14,Fintroduced by Mark Isherwood MS
OL,15,Fearlier this year to promote and
OL,16,Ffacilitate the use of BSL in Wales. If
OL,17,Fpassed, it would establish duties for
OL,18,FWelsh ministers and public bodies, and
OL,19,Fappoint a BSL advisor who would
OL,20,Fsupport the implementation.
