OL,3,CShortage of BSL interpreters 'putting
OL,4,Cnew law's success in doubt'
OL,6,FOne of the key impacts of the law
OL,7,Fwould be requiring local authorities
OL,8,Fand health boards to publish BSL plans
OL,9,Fon how they would promote the use of
OL,10,Fthe language.
OL,12,FThe aims of the Bill have been
OL,13,Fwelcomed by campaigners and BSL
OL,14,Fspeakers, including Stephen Brattan-
OL,15,FWilson, a BSL interpreter based in
OL,16,FCardiff who says the Bill is necessary
OL,17,Fbecause the Equality Act 2010 does not
OL,18,Fadequately provide protections for
OL,19,Flanguage.
