OL,3,CShortage of BSL interpreters 'putting
OL,4,Cnew law's success in doubt'
OL,6,FThe Equality Act 2010 imposes a duty
OL,7,Fon public bodies to make "reasonable
OL,8,Fadjustments" for people who are
OL,9,Fdisabled. However, Stephen says this
OL,10,Fmeans Deaf people have to self-
OL,11,Fidentify as disabled to exercise their
OL,12,Frights under the law.
OL,14,FHe hopes the BSL Bill would mean
OL,15,Fpublic bodies have a duty to provide
OL,16,FBSL provisions rather than waiting for
OL,17,Fa complaint under the Equality Act,
OL,18,Fand then providing support.
