OL,3,CShortage of BSL interpreters 'putting
OL,4,Cnew law's success in doubt'
OL,6,FA Welsh Government spokesperson said
OL,7,Fit is committed to "strengthening
OL,8,FBritish Sign Language provision across
OL,9,FWelsh public services and creating a
OL,10,FWales that respects and values BSL as
OL,11,Fa vital part of our society," adding:
OL,12,F"We have worked with stakeholders to
OL,13,Fdevelop recommendations that aim to
OL,14,Fimprove access to services and
OL,15,Finformation for deaf BSL signers. We
OL,16,Fwelcome and support Mark Isherwood's
OL,17,FBSL (Wales) Bill, which will help
OL,18,Fdeliver our shared goals of promoting
OL,19,Fand facilitating the use of BSL in
OL,20,FWales."
